verbose_text: Compared with the PMA group, V. axillare high-dose + PMA group had significantly lower NF-kappaB, TNF-alpha, IkappaBalpha, and IKKbeta levels, which indicated V. axillare inhibited the activation of NF-kappaB pathway by PMA, and in turn supported that V. axillare protected GES-1 from alcohol damage by blocking the NF-kappaB pathway.
evidence: IKKbeta levels, which indicated V. axillare inhibited the activation of NF-kappaB
